criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  score on MABC-2 below the 15th percentile;

          -  score on DCDQ-Brazil below age expectation, indicating problems on everyday living
             and/or academic skills;

          -  cognitive development within the expected age range according to the Wechsler
             Intelligence Scale for Children-Fourth Edition (WISC-IV);

          -  no diagnosis or signs of neurological or neuromuscular diseases.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  no reading ability;

          -  child refuses to participate on assessment sessions.
